§ LICENSING (per-tier · clarity)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

§ TIER-A (open) :
  ⊑ MIT-or-Apache-2.0 dual-license · permissive · attribution-required · no-warranty
  ⊑ "Powered-by-CSSL" badge encouraged for-derivative-projects
  ⊑ contributor-license-agreement (CLA) for-larger-PRs (joint-copyright with-Apocky)

§ TIER-B (proprietary) :
  ⊑ End-User-License-Agreement (EULA) · per-jurisdiction · auto-generated via Termly/iubenda
  ⊑ NO-reverse-engineering clause · NO-redistribute clause · refund-rights respected (jurisdiction-mandated)
  ⊑ in-game-content owned-by-player (Ascended-items · Home-decorations · cosmetics) · transferable @ Bazaar
  ⊑ trained-KAN-weights are-Apocky-IP · ¬ player-owned · ¬ resellable

§ TIER-C (server) :
  ⊑ NOT-licensed-to-anyone · server-private
  ⊑ players have-data-subject-rights (GDPR · CCPA) · export + delete on-request · always

§ TIER-D (player-private) :
  ⊑ player owns-fully · Apocky has-NO-claim · Apocky-cannot-access (cryptographic-impossibility)

§ TIER-E (protocol) :
  ⊑ documented-publicly @ open-source TIER-A specs · enables-third-party-clients (within EULA-bounds)
  ⊑ schema-versioned · backward-compatible-where-possible

