§ LEGAL-AUTONOMOUS-SETUP (Apocky : "I don't want paperwork")
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

§ AUTONOMOUS-PATH @ minimize-paperwork via-services-that-handle-it
  ⊑ INCORPORATION : Stripe-Atlas (~$500 one-time) · Delaware-C-Corp · automated-EIN · 1-week
  ⊑ ToS + EULA + Privacy : Termly OR iubenda (~$10/month) · auto-jurisdictional
  ⊑ Tax : Stripe-Tax (auto-VAT/GST/sales-tax) + Stripe-Atlas-Bookkeeping (~$25/month)
  ⊑ Trademarks : LegalZoom OR Trademarkia (~$250 each) for-Labyrinth-of-Apocalypse + CSSL + Ouroboroid
  ⊑ Compliance : Termly handles-COPPA + CCPA + GDPR + ePrivacy auto-update
  ⊑ Gambling-law (gacha) : per spec/13 monetization is-strictly-cosmetic · transparent-rates · pity-system · BE/NL-jurisdiction-block
  ⊑ Music-licensing : ONLY CC0-or-CC-BY for-procgen-seeds · ¬ commercial-music · OR auto-cleared via Epidemic Sound API integration
  ⊑ Payment-processor : Stripe (handles PCI-DSS-SAQ-A) · NEVER-touch-raw-card-data
  ⊑ Hosting-compliance : Vercel + Supabase are SOC-2 + GDPR-compliant out-of-the-box

§ TOTAL-AUTONOMOUS-COST @ year-1 startup
  ⊑ Stripe-Atlas      : $500 one-time
  ⊑ Termly+iubenda    : ~$120/year
  ⊑ Stripe-Tax        : ~$300/year (small-revenue) · scales with revenue
  ⊑ Trademarks (3)    : $750 one-time
  ⊑ Domain + email    : ~$50/year
  ⊑ Vercel-Pro        : $240/year (when-needed)
  ⊑ Supabase-Pro      : $300/year (when-needed)
  ⊑ Stripe-fees       : 2.9% + $0.30 per-transaction (industry-standard)
  ⊑ TOTAL-Y1          : ~$2,260 fixed-overhead + variable revenue-share
  ⊑ Apocky-time-investment : ~5-10 hours total (Stripe-Atlas-form · Termly-config · trademark-form · ToS-review)

§ AUTONOMOUS-DEFENSE @ ¬ legal-bullshit
  ⊑ Stripe-Atlas handles : C-Corp · EIN · banking · post-incorporation
  ⊑ Termly handles : ToS · Privacy-Policy · Cookie-Policy · jurisdictional-updates
  ⊑ Stripe-Tax handles : VAT/GST/sales-tax-collection-and-remittance
  ⊑ Apocky-only-touches : Stripe-Atlas-form (1×) · Termly-config (1×) · trademark-form (3×)
  ⊑ ALL-ELSE automated · ¬ ongoing-paperwork

§ INSURANCE @ when-revenue-justifies
  ⊑ general-liability + cyber-liability + E&O · via Hiscox or Next Insurance · ~$500-1000/year
  ⊑ NOT-required-for-launch · add when revenue > $100K/year

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
§ ANTI-PIRACY + ANTI-CHEAT (binary protection · server-authoritative-monetization)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

§ binary-protection
  ⊑ Steam-DRM @ default · Steamworks anti-tamper-API for-launcher-only
  ⊑ stripped-symbols + LTO @ release · lift-and-shift attackers face-recompile-effort
  ⊑ KAN-weights Ed25519-signed · ¬ valid-without-master-pubkey-verification · refuses-to-load-if-modified
  ⊑ asset-bundle BLAKE3-integrity · refuses-to-load-if-tampered

§ server-authoritative monetization
  ⊑ Stripe-checkout-server-side · client never-sees-Stripe-secret-key
  ⊑ entitlement-DB @ Supabase · server-of-truth for-cosmetic-ownership · Aetheric-Shards-balance · battle-pass-tier
  ⊑ client-shows-cosmetic-equip but server-validates-entitlement on-equip-action
  ⊑ Σ-Chain Coherence-Proof catches client-state-divergence (¬ Coherence-Score = harm-flag · attestation-axis-EconomicTransparency)

§ what's-NOT-server-authoritative @ deliberate-anti-pattern
  ⊑ pure-gameplay (combat · crafting · spell-cast) is-CLIENT-SIDE for-latency
  ⊑ asynchronous-validation @ server samples 1% of replay-frames · validates Coherence-Score-deterministically
  ⊑ flagged-replay-divergence → ban-after-3-strikes per anti-cheat-policy
  ⊑ NEVER-server-authoritative gameplay-physics (rollback-netcode-style untenable for-deep-substrate)

§ what's-DELIBERATELY-OPEN @ build-community
  ⊑ specs are-public · implementations are-private · this-asymmetry-IS-the-moat
  ⊑ third-party-clients ALLOWED within-EULA · ¬ allowed-to-cheat · ¬ allowed-to-bypass-monetization
  ⊑ modding-API @ TIER-A open · cosmetic-mods OK · gameplay-balance-mods limited-to-private-runs
  ⊑ private-runs (single-player + invite-only) accept-mods · public-multiverse refuses-non-canonical-state

